# zeroMatrix

- _zeroMatrix(anInteger, anotherInteger)_

Answers the `zero` matrix of the specified shape.

A 2×2 matrix:

```
>>> 2.zeroMatrix(2)
[0 0; 0 0]
```

A 2×3 matrix:

```
>>> 2.zeroMatrix(3)
[0 0 0; 0 0 0]
```

A 3×2 matrix:

```
>>> 3.zeroMatrix(2)
[0 0; 0 0; 0 0]
```

* * *

See also: identityMatrix, reshape
